<h1>Paul Burdick</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://reedmaniac.com/now">reedmaniac.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Portland
OR
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
I have been an outdoor guide, web developer, VP Engineering, and Chief Technology Officer but at my core I like to think of myself as a Geek.
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
Eternal student and explorer.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
The Universe is so vast and beautiful. Human civilization and culture is so fantastic and our potential seemingly endless. I cannot imagine a day when I am not trying to learn or build something new.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
The constraints of reality are antithetical to my goals.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
"The Name of the Wind" by Patrick Rothfuss.
</p>

